17 REIMBURSEMENTS FROM A THIRD–PARTY PAYOR;
18 (III) MAY NOT BE SUBJECT TO AN OPEN APPEAL WITH AN
19 INSURANCE COMPANY; AND
20 (IV) MUST BE FOR AN INDIVIDUAL WHOSE FAMILY INCOME IS AT
21 OR BELOW 500% OF THE FEDERAL POVERTY LEVEL OR WHO HAS MEDICAL DEBT
22 EXCEEDING 5% OF THE INDIVIDUAL’S FAMILY INCOME, AS DETERMINED BY THE
23 GOVERNMENTAL UNIT OR CONTRACTOR PURCHASING THE DEBT.
24 (3) DEBT SOLD UNDER THIS SUBSECTION MAY BE SOLD WITH A
25 REDUCTION OF COMMISSION CHARGES.
